{"id":784,"parent_id":0,"book_id":8,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":784,"title":"Levites","subtitle":"","short_title":"Levites","uri":"/scriptures/bd/levites","content":[["div",{"id":"t1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/levites.t1","order":".000.2070"},[".title","Levites"],["div",{"id":"p1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/levites.p1","order":".000.2071"},"Descendants of Levi. The work of ministering in the sanctuary was assigned to this tribe. The Levites are sometimes spoken of as distinct from the priests (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-kgs/8.4"},"1 Kgs. 8:4"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ezra/2.70"},"Ezra 2:70"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/1.19"},"John 1:19"],"); sometimes as though all Levites were also priests, “the priests, the Levites” (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/deut/18.1"},"Deut. 18:1"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/josh/3.3"},"Josh. 3:3"],"). The work of the Levites was to assist the priests (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/num/3.5-10"},"Num. 3:5–10"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/num/18.1-7"},"18:1–7"],"). They acted as musicians (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-chr/6.16,31"},"1 Chr. 6:16, 31"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-chr/15.16"},"15:16"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/neh/11.17,22"},"Neh. 11:17, 22"],"); slaughtered the sacrifices (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/2-chr/29.34"},"2 Chr. 29:34"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/2-chr/35.11"},"35:11"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ezra/6.20"},"Ezra 6:20"],"); and generally assisted in the temple (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/neh/11.16,19"},"Neh. 11:16, 19"],"). The Levites were themselves offered as a wave-offering on behalf of the children of Israel (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/num/8.11-15"},"Num. 8:11–15"],"); they thus became God’s peculiar property, given to Him in place of the firstborn (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/num/8.16"},"8:16"],"). They were cleansed for their office (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/num/8.7-16"},"8:7–16"],"). They had no inheritance in Canaan (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/num/18.23-24"},"18:23–24"],"); but they had the tithe (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/num/18.21"},"18:21"],"), 48 cities (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/num/35.6"},"35:6"],"), and a claim on the alms of the people at feast times (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/deut/12.18-19"},"Deut. 12:18–19"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/deut/14.27-29"},"14:27–29"],")."]]],"refs":null}
